'''Aaron Tshibola''' (born 2 January 1995) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] for {{Scottish football updater|Kilmarno}} club [[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock]]. Born in England, he represents the [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]].

Born in London, he came through the youth ranks at [[Reading F.C.|Reading]] before moving to [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] in 2016. He has had loan spells at English [[Football League]] sides [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]], [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] and [[Milton Keynes Dons F.C.|Milton Keynes Dons]], as well as [[Scottish Premiership]] side [[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock]]. He has also played in Belgium for [[Waasland Beveren]] and in Portugal for [[C.D. Aves|Aves]].

==Early life==
Tshibola was born in the [[London Borough of Newham]] in England.<ref name="ENFA">{{cite web |title=Player search |url=http://www.enfa.co.uk/ |publisher=English National Football Archive |accessdate=11 December 2014 |url-access=registration}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Reading===
Tshibola joined [[Reading F.C.|Reading]]'s academy at age thirteen<ref name="Reading profile">{{cite web |title=Aaron Tshibola |url=http://www.readingfc.co.uk/team/player-profile/aaron-tshibola/18 |publisher=Reading F.C |accessdate=23 August 2014 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141008042010/http://www.readingfc.co.uk/team/player-profile/aaron-tshibola/18 |archive-date=8 October 2014 |url-status=dead}}</ref> and signed his first professional deal with the club in March 2011.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.readingfc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10306~2304375,00.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110305235650/http://www.readingfc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0%2C%2C10306~2304375%2C00.html |archive-date=5 March 2011 |title=Tanner and Tshibola sign on |publisher=Reading F.C |accessdate=28 March 2015 |url-status=dead}}</ref> While in the Reading Academy, Tshibola went on trial with [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]].<ref>{{cite news |title=MAN UTD TRIALS FOR READING ACADEMY PAIR |url=http://www.tribalfootball.com/articles/man-utd-trials-reading-academy-pair-3071991#.VRcYhPmsWSo |publisher=Tribal Football |accessdate=28 March 2015}}</ref>

Ahead of the 2014–15 season, Tshibola signed a new contract with [[Reading F.C.|Reading]], keeping him at the club until 2016.<ref>{{cite news |title=Transfer news: Reading midfielder Aaron Tshibola signs new two-year deal |url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11756/9355885/transfer-news-reading-midfielder-aaron-tshibola-signs-new-two-year-deal |publisher=Sky Sports |date=20 June 2014 |accessdate=28 March 2015}}</ref> Then on 23 August 2014, he made his professional debut as an 86th-minute substitute in a [[Football League Championship|Championship]] fixture against [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Nottingham Forest 4–0 Reading |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/28815166 |publisher=BBC Sport |accessdate=5 October 2014}}</ref>

On 9 September 2015, Tshibola extended his contract with Reading until the summer of 2019.<ref name="Aaron Tshibola awarded new Royals contract">{{cite web |title=Aaron Tshibola awarded new Royals contract |url=http://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/article/aaron-tshibola-new-contract-reading-fc-2677572.aspx |website=readingfc.co.uk/ |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=9 September 2015 |date=9 September 2015}}</ref>

On 2 January 2015, he moved to [[Football League Two|League Two]] side [[Hartlepool United F.C.|Hartlepool United]] on a one-month loan deal,<ref name="Tshibola joins Hartlepool United on loan">{{Cite news |title=Tshibola joins Hartlepool on loan |url=http://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/article/aaron-tshibola-hartlepool-united-reading-2177442.aspx |publisher=Reading F.C |date=2 January 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150105180532/http://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/article/aaron-tshibola-hartlepool-united-reading-2177442.aspx |archive-date=5 January 2015 |url-status=dead}}</ref> before making his debut the next day in a 1–0 loss against [[Wycombe Wanderers F.C.|Wycombe Wanderers]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Wycombe Wanderers 1–0 Hartlepool United |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/30609068 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=3 January 2015 |accessdate=28 March 2015}}</ref> His first four appearances at the club earned Tshibola a loan extension until the end of the season.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/article/aaron-tshibola-hartlepool-united-reading-2235172.aspx |title=Tshibola extends Hartlepool loan |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=28 March 2015 |date=29 January 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150328213304/http://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/article/aaron-tshibola-hartlepool-united-reading-2235172.aspx |archive-date=28 March 2015 |url-status=dead}}</ref> His loan spell extension led manager [[Ronnie Moore]] to thank Tshibola for his commitment at Hartlepool United.<ref>{{cite news |title=Hartlepool boss Ronnie Moore thanks Aaron Tshibola for loyalty |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/31096288 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=3 February 2015|access-date=28 March 2015}}</ref> He was then awarded [[Man of the match]], in a 3–2 win over [[Plymouth Argyle F.C.|Plymouth Argyle]] after an impressive performance when he assisted one of the goals in the game.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/article/aaron-tshibola-dominic-samuel-reaidng-fc-coventry-2248162.aspx |title=Loan Round Up: Tshibola man of the match |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=28 March 2015 |date=4 February 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150328213040/http://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/article/aaron-tshibola-dominic-samuel-reaidng-fc-coventry-2248162.aspx |archive-date=28 March 2015 |url-status=dead}}</ref>

===Aston Villa===
On 10 July 2016, Tshibola moved to [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] on a four-year contract, for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web |title=Tshibola completes Villa Park move |url=http://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/article/2016-17/tshibola-departs-madejski-stadium-to-sign-for-aston-villa-3177097.aspx |website=readingfc.co.uk |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=10 July 2016 |date=10 July 2016}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club in a 1–1 draw with [[Newcastle United]] on 24 September 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/37392374 |title=Aston Villa 1–1 Newcastle |publisher=BBC |date=24 September 2016 |accessdate=27 September 2016}}</ref> On 30 January 2017, Tshibola moved to [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]] on loan for the remainder of the [[2016–17 EFL Championship|2016–17]] season.<ref>{{cite web |title=Tshibola joins The Reds |url=http://www.nottinghamforest.co.uk/news/article/2016-17/nottingham-forest-aston-villa-aaron-tshibola-3545100.aspx |website=nottinghamforest.co.uk |publisher=Nottingham Forest |accessdate=30 January 2017 |date=30 January 2017}}</ref>

On 27 July 2017, Tshibola joined [[EFL League One]] side [[Milton Keynes Dons F.C.|Milton Keynes Dons]] on a season-long loan deal.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Aston Villa midfielder joins League One side on season-long loan |url=http://www.birminghammail.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/aston-villa-midfielder-joins-league-13396962 |publisher=Birmingham Mail |date=27 July 2017 |accessdate=27 July 2017}}</ref> He scored his first goal for MK Dons in an [[EFL Trophy]] tie against [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C. Reserves and Academy|Brighton & Hove Albion Under-23s]] on 29 August 2017.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.miltonkeynes.co.uk/sport/football/mk-dons/report-mk-dons-2-0-brighton-u21s-routine-win-in-checkatrade-trophy-1-8126085 |title=REPORT: MK Dons 2–0 Brighton U21s: Routine win in Checkatrade Trophy |publisher=miltonkeynes.co.uk |date=29 August 2017 |accessdate=30 August 2017|archive-date=30 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170830160912/http://www.miltonkeynes.co.uk/sport/football/mk-dons/report-mk-dons-2-0-brighton-u21s-routine-win-in-checkatrade-trophy-1-8126085|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 9 November 2017, he returned to Aston Villa following the mutual termination of his loan with Milton Keynes Dons.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/41928507 |title=Aaron Tshibola: Aston Villa midfielder's loan with MK Dons is cancelled |publisher=BBC Sport |date=9 November 2017 |accessdate=14 November 2017}}</ref>

===Kilmarnock===
Tshibola was loaned to [[Scottish Premiership]] club [[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock]] in January 2018, working under his former [[Reading F.C.|Reading]] manager [[Steve Clarke]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42858245 |title=Aaron Tshibola: Kilmarnock sign Aston Villa midfielder on loan |work=BBC Sport |publisher=BBC |date=29 January 2018 |accessdate=29 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.birminghammail.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/what-aston-villas-forgotten-man-15081512 |title=This is what Aston Villa's forgotten man is set to do now |date=28 August 2018}}</ref> He made his debut for Killie on 3 February 2018, as a 65th minute substitute for [[Kris Boyd]] in the Ayrshire side's 1–0 win over [[Scottish Premiership]] Champions [[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42842297 |title=Kilmarnock 1–0 Celtic |work=BBC Sport}}</ref> Tshibola scored his first Kilmarnock goal in the 4–0 [[Scottish Cup]] win over [[Brora Rangers F.C.|Brora Rangers]] the following week.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/42927889 |title=Kilmarnock 4–0 Brora Rangers |work=BBC Sport}}</ref> After six months, he returned to Aston Villa, only to be loaned back out to Kilmarnock for another season on 29 August 2018.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.avfc.co.uk/News/2018/08/29/tshibola-rejoins-kilmarnock-on-loan |title=Aaron Tshibola rejoins Kilmarnock on season-long loan |date=29 August 2018 |publisher=Aston Villa FC|access-date=29 August 2018}}</ref>

===Waasland Beveren===
On 29 August 2019, Tshibola signed for Belgian club [[Waasland Beveren]] for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web |title=WELKOM, AARON TSHIBOLA! |date=29 August 2019 |url=https://www.waasland-beveren.be/2019/08/welkom-aaron-tshibola/ |publisher=[[Waasland Beveren]] |accessdate=29 August 2019 |archive-date=30 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190830042451/https://www.waasland-beveren.be/2019/08/welkom-aaron-tshibola/ |url-status=dead}}</ref> On 19 October 2019, he made his debut in a 2–0 defeat to [[K.A.A. Gent|Gent]].

===Aves===
On 31 January 2020, Tshibola signed for Portuguese side [[C.D. Aves|Aves]] on a one-and-a-half-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://cdaves.pt/contratacao-aaron-tshibola/ |title=CONTRATAÇÃO {{!}} AARON TSHIBOLA|date=31 January 2020|website=Clube Desportivo Das Aves|access-date=1 February 2020|archive-date=1 February 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201091427/http://cdaves.pt/contratacao-aaron-tshibola/|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 1 March 2020, he made his debut, coming on as substitute in a 3–1 defeat to [[F.C. Paços de Ferreira|Paços de Ferreira]]. He made one other appearance in a 2–0 defeat to [[Sporting CP]] before the league was suspended due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic in Portugal]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://ligaportugal.vsports.pt/mday/1732/liga/ |title=LIGA NOS Época 2019/2020 |date=8 March 2020 |website=Liga NOS Official Website|access-date=31 March 2020}}</ref>

On 13 July 2020, Tshibola announced on his [[Twitter]] account that due to financial difficulties at the club, he had left Aves and was a free agent once again.<ref>{{Cite web |date=13 July 2020 |title=Aaron Tshibola – Twitter |url=https://twitter.com/AaronTshibola/status/1282626837357760512|access-date=13 July 2020 |website=Twitter}}</ref>

===Kilmarnock===
On 31 July 2020, Tshibola returned for a third spell with [[Kilmarnock F.C.|Kilmarnock]], signing a one-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kilmarnock sign Aaron Tshibola for third time after relegation double |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/53613633 |date=31 July 2020 |accessdate=1 August 2020 |website=BBC Sport}}</ref> He left Kilmarnock at the end of the 2020–21 season.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://kilmarnockfc.co.uk/news/squad-update-following-2020-21-season/ |title=Squad update following 2020/21 season |date=25 May 2021}}</ref>

===Gençlerbirliği===
In July 2021, Tshibola signed for Turkish side [[Gençlerbirliği S.K.|Gençlerbirliği]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nottheoldfirm.com/news/aaron-tshibola-signs-for-genclerbirligi-sk-after-kilmarnock-exit/ |title=Aaron Tshibola signs for Gençlerbirliği SK after Kilmarnock exit |website=nottheoldfirm.com |date=11 July 2021|access-date=11 July 2021}}</ref> He made his debut playing 90 minutes of a 0–0 draw with [[Adanaspor]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Adanaspor vs. Gençlerbirliği – 21 August 2021 |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2021/08/21/turkey/1-lig/adanaspor-fk/genclerbirligi/3557621/|access-date=23 August 2021 |website=Soccerway}}</ref> On 19 December 2021, he scored his first goal in Turkish football, in a 5–0 victory over [[Menemenspor]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Gençlerbirliği vs. Menemenspor – 19 December 2021 |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2021/12/19/turkey/1-lig/genclerbirligi/yeni-menemen-belediyespor-izmir/3557764/|access-date=25 January 2022 |website=Soccerway}}</ref>

===AEL Limassol===
On 12 August 2022, [[Cypriot First Division]] club [[AEL Limassol]] announced that Tshibola had joined the club.<ref>{{Citation |title=Welcome Aaron Tshibola! Let's Go Lions 🔥🟡🔵 {{!}} By AEL Limassol FC {{!}} Facebook |url=https://ms-my.facebook.com/OfficialAELFC/videos/welcome-aaron-tshibola-lets-go-lions-/590784499417723/ |language=en |access-date=24 August 2022}}</ref> He made his debut of the club on 28 August 2022, in a 2–1 away defeat to local rivals [[Aris Limassol FC|Aris Limassol]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=28 August 2022 |title=Aris Limassol 2 : 1 AEL Limassol |url=https://www.whoscored.com/Matches/1662193/Show/Cyprus-First-Division-2022-2023-Aris-Limassol-AEL-Limassol |access-date=28 October 2022 |website=www.whoscored.com}}</ref> He scored his first goal in Cyprus on 28 October 2022, in a 3–0 victory over [[Akritas Chlorakas]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Akritas vs. AEL – 28 October 2022 |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2022/10/28/cyprus/1-division/akritas-chloraka/ael-limassol/3840456/ |access-date=28 October 2022 |website=Soccerway}}</ref>

===Hatta Club===
In August 2023, Tshibola joined newly promoted [[UAE Pro League]] team [[Hatta Club]] for a €150,000 fee.<ref>{{Cite web |date=11 August 2023 |title=Announcement |url=https://www.ael-fc.com/2023/08/tsimpola/ |access-date=11 August 2023 |website=www.ael-fc.com}}</ref>

After half a season with [[PAS Lamia 1964|Lamia]], Tshibola joined [[Super League Greece|Greek Super League]] club [[Levadiakos F.C.|Levadiakos]] in June 2025.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.novasports.gr/sport/podosfairo/event/super-league-1/article/14256406/apo-ti-lamia-ston-levadeiako/ |title=Από τη Λαμία στον Λεβαδειακό |website=novasports.gr |date=19 June 2025 |accessdate=19 June 2025 |language=Greek}}</ref>

===Kilmarnock (third spell)===
On 2 February 2026, Tshibola returned to Scottish Premiership club Kilmarnock on a permanent deal.<ref> {{cite web |url=https://kilmarnockfc.co.uk/news/aaron-tshibola-returns-to-kilmarnock-on-permanent-deal/ |title=Aaron Tshibola returns to Kilmanock on permanent deal |website=kilmarnockfc.co.uk |date=2 February 2026 |accessdate=2 February 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
Tshibola was called up by [[England national under-18 football team|England U18]] and made his debut, coming on as a substitute in the second half, in a 1–0 loss against [[Belgium national under-18 football team|Belgium]] on 5 March 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/article/england-trio-play-tonight-695061.aspx |title=Trio make England bow |publisher=Reading F.C. |accessdate=28 March 2015 |date=6 March 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150328215222/http://www.readingfc.co.uk/news/article/england-trio-play-tonight-695061.aspx |archive-date=28 March 2015 |url-status=dead}}</ref>

He is also eligible to represent [[DR Congo national football team|DR Congo national team]] due to his ancestry.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://thetilehurstend.sbnation.com/2013/8/6/4593404/the-aaron-tshibola-interview-reading-fc |title=The Aaron Tshibola Interview |date=6 August 2013 |publisher=SB Nation.com |accessdate=10 July 2016}}</ref> He was called up to the DR Congo national team for a friendly against [[Kenya national football team|Kenya]] on 26 March 2017, but did not make an appearance.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rdcongoleopardsfoot.com/amical-kenya-rd-congo-la-liste-des-24leopards/ |title=Amical Kenya-RD Congo: La liste des 24 Léopards |date=20 March 2017}}</ref> On 27 March 2018, he finally made his senior international debut for DR Congo, playing 45 minutes in a friendly against [[Tanzania national football team|Tanzania]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2018/03/27/world/friendlies/tanzania/congo-dr/2749056/?ICID=HP_MS_01_0 |title=TANZANIA VS. CONGO DR (Match report) |publisher=Soccerway |date=27 March 2018 |accessdate=27 March 2018}}</ref>

Tshibola was called up to the DR Congo squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] on 20 May 2026, replacing the injured [[Rocky Bushiri]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.edinburghnews.scotsman.com/sport/football/hibs/hibs-defender-rocky-bushiri-opens-up-on-world-cup-injury-heartache-and-makes-vow-8614513 |title=Hibs defender Rocky Bushiri opens up on World Cup injury heartache and makes vow |publisher=[[Edinburgh Evening News]] |first=Mark |last=Atkinson |date=May 21, 2026 |access-date=May 21, 2026 |url-status=live |archive-date=May 21, 2026 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20260521161743/https://www.edinburghnews.scotsman.com/sport/football/hibs/hibs-defender-rocky-bushiri-opens-up-on-world-cup-injury-heartache-and-makes-vow-8614513}}</ref>

